ties and private foundations are invited to meet with Dr  Dellinger  Information regarding internship positions with Spanish companies is also available for cadets with a high intermediate or advanced level of language proficiency   De Madrid al cielo    Dr  Mary Ann Dellinger Home Awards and Honors Courses Publications Conference Papers Professional Citizenship Cadet Development Summer in Spain VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 